# Example Synthetic Phenotype Dataset (Large)

## Description

This is a placeholder dataset for testing complex annotation scenarios.
It contains comprehensive phenotypic data with 20+ columns and 10 participants,
including demographics, clinical assessments, and MRI imaging metadata.

**PLACEHOLDER**: Replace `participants.tsv` with your own anonymized dataset.

## Dataset Characteristics

- **Participants**: 10 subjects (6 with Parkinson's disease, 4 controls)
- **Columns**: 16 phenotypic variables covering demographics, clinical status, and imaging
- **Types**: Mix of continuous (age, scores) and categorical (sex, condition, medication)

## Column Reference

| Column | Type | Description | Examples |
|--------|------|---|---|
| participant_id | string | Unique identifier | sub-001, sub-002 |
| age | continuous | Age in years | 45-67 |
| sex | categorical | Biological sex | M, F |
| condition | categorical | Clinical group | PD, CTRL |
| scanner | categorical | MRI scanner | 3T_SIEMENS_PRISMA |
| disease_duration | continuous | Disease duration in years | 0-15 |
| medication_status | categorical | Medication regimen | levodopa, none, combinations |
| mmse_score | continuous | Mini-Mental State Exam | 19-30 |
| updrs_total | continuous | UPDRS total score | 0-84 |
| updrs_motor | continuous | UPDRS motor score | 0-52 |
| updrs_cognitive | continuous | UPDRS cognitive score | 0-12 |
| mri_field_strength | continuous | Field strength (Tesla) | 1.5, 3 |
| mri_protocol | categorical | MRI sequence | T1w_T2w, T1w_FLAIR |
| assessment_date | date | Assessment date | YYYY-MM-DD |
| cognitive_status | categorical | Cognitive classification | normal, MCI, dementia |
| disease_subtype | categorical | PD subtype or NA | tremor, rigid, mixed, NA |

## BIDS Compliance

This dataset follows BIDS format for phenotypic data.
See [BIDS Phenotypic Data](https://bids-specification.readthedocs.io/en/stable/03-modality-agnostic-files.html#phenotypic-data) specification.

## Neurobagel Annotation

This dataset is designed for testing Neurobagel phenotype annotation with:
- Multiple clinical assessment variables (UPDRS, MMSE)
- Disease-related variables (disease_duration, subtype)
- Imaging metadata (scanner, protocol, field strength)
- Mixed variable types for testing categorical and continuous handling

## Instructions for Use

1. Replace synthetic data with your own anonymized dataset (maintain structure)
2. Keep column names for compatibility with annotation tests
3. Update README and CHANGES with your actual dataset info
4. Verify phenotypic data meets BIDS phenotypic format
